# Silasya Earth — Digital Product Passport Backend
### Python (Flask) + MySQL · Production-Ready

---

## Project Structure

```
silasya_dpp/
├── run.py                      # Entry point
├── requirements.txt
├── .env.example
├── schema.sql                  # Full MySQL schema (run this first)
├── config/
│   └── settings.py             # All config from .env
└── app/
    ├── __init__.py             # App factory
    ├── db.py                   # MySQL connection + query helpers
    ├── routes/
    │   ├── auth.py             # Register, login, profile
    │   ├── passport.py         # PUBLIC QR scan endpoint (all 7 layers)
    │   ├── products.py         # Layer 1 — Product Identification
    │   ├── layer2.py           # Layer 2 — Raw Material Traceability
    │   ├── layer3.py           # Layer 3 — Manufacturing / Artisan Story
    │   ├── layer4.py           # Layer 4 — Environmental Impact
    │   ├── layer5.py           # Layer 5 — Circularity & Recyclability
    │   ├── layer6.py           # Layer 6 — Performance & Care
    │   ├── layer7.py           # Layer 7 — Blockchain Verification
    │   ├── certs.py            # Compliance Certificates (GOTS, UFLPA, ESPR...)
    │   ├── artisans.py         # Artisan profiles
    │   ├── clusters.py         # Artisan clusters
    │   └── admin.py            # Admin dashboard analytics
    └── utils/
        ├── auth.py             # JWT helpers + require_auth decorator
        ├── blockchain.py       # SHA-256 hash chain logic
        └── helpers.py          # Response helpers, pagination, serialiser
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Database
mysql -u root -p < schema.sql

# 2. Environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — set DB_PASSWORD and SECRET_KEY

# 3. Install
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Run
python run.py
# API available at http://localhost:5000
```

